f=Brand Studio/weave/marketplace/brand-storytelling/SKILL.md · tx=<!-- Unmodified copy "brand-storytelling" (RefoundAI/lenny-skills, 1.1k★ repo family marcus's setting-okrs-goals source), fulfilling catalog's storytelling-frameworks slot. Chosen over generic hero's-journey/Pixar-spine writeups because distills frameworks THROUGH named practitioners tactical advice insight: Pixar spine (Moesta), hero's-journey casting (Petra Wille), customer-as-hero/Obi-Wan (Maples), five-second moment stakes toolkit (Matthew Dicks), movement framing rallying cry (Raskin), memification (Yamashata), dinner-test repeatability (Meservey), start-in-the-action (Merci Grace), problems-beat-successes (Feifer). ROLE SYSTEM: weave's CRAFT layer any single chapter hooks, lands moment, gets retold. ARCHITECTURE layer (which chapter is, whether exist, continuity) weave's custom brand-story-arcs skill, whose checks cite craft. chapters approved brand-story-arcs get built skill's techniques, worded lena, gated spark. --> · h1:Brand Storytelling=Help user craft compelling narratives make their brand memorable using techniques product leaders storytelling experts. · h:to Help=user asks help brand storytelling: **Understand context** Ask who audience (investors, customers, employees) what action they want inspire **Find core story** Help identify transformation, movement, unique insight heart brand **Structure narrative** Apply proven frameworks organize story effectively **Make memorable** Help craft specific phrases, metaphors, moments stick · h3:Lead movement, don't solve problem=Andy Raskin: "This structure about defining movement—that's different 'I'm going solve your problem.'" Frame your brand leader shift toward new way winning. · h3:Story before product=Brian Chesky: "One first things figure out what story is. story often dictates product. story helpful way develop cohesive product." Define narrative before finalizing features. · h3:Find the five-second moment=Matthew Dicks: "Every story about singular moment—I call five seconds. moment transformation realization. 98% story provides context make moment clear." Identify single moment change. · h3:Start middle action=Merci Grace: "Every pitch start middle action, like Mission Impossible. Tom Cruise always doing crazy shit before actual mission. gets attention." Skip boring setup—hook them immediately. · h3:Problems beat successes=Jason Feifer: "Success stories aren't interesting. Problem-solving stories are. Frame your story around specific challenge you faced counterintuitive way you solved it." · h3:You're Obi-Wan, not Luke=Mike Maples Jr: "The customer hero (Luke Skywalker), founder mentor (Obi-Wan) providing tools. Position your product lightsaber—the tool hero needs." · h3:Make it repeatable=Lulu Cheng Meservey: "Make memorable. Make people want say their volition. Use analogies, colorful mental images, jokes. Replace adjectives anecdotes people repeat dinner." · h3:Paint emotional pictures=Camille Ricketts: "Effective storytelling paints emotional picture vision. Convey emotional quality mission, technical details, enlist hearts minds." · h3:Hook, message, celebration=Christina Wodtke: beginning, middle, end. Intrigue hook—a mystery, secret, surprise. middle delivers message. Always end success celebration." · h3:Memify your insights=Yuhki Yamashata: "The goal 'memification'—synthesize insights they're catchy enough execs cite meetings. Use metaphors explain complex concepts." · h2:Questions to Help Users="Who your audience what you want them after hearing this?", "What's transformation realization heart your story?", "What problem you face others relate to?", "Can someone repeat your core message dinner party?", "Are you hero story, your customer?" · h2:Common Mistakes to Flag=**Starting your company** Start audience's problem world's change, "We are...", **Feature lists instead stories** Stories about change; lists forgettable, **Hero syndrome** Position yourself mentor, hero, **Vague vision** "Making world better" isn't story; specific, **No stakes** nothing's risk, there's tension · h2:Deep Dive=insights guests, see `references/guest-insights.md` · h2:Related Skills=Positioning & Messaging, Giving Presentations, Fundraising, Media Relations